paragraphs.title: Syntax to create the Cloudmart database
paragraphs.text:
%md

#### Creating the Cloudmart database
It may be possible to create the Cloudmart database remotely. The following syntax will work if the user postgres is allowed remote access.
If this fails then this database will have to be created on the database host.

~~~
export PGPASSWORD='BadPass%1'; psql -h db01.cloudair.lan -U postgres -d postgres -p 5432  <<EOF
        CREATE USER devuser WITH PASSWORD 'BadPass%1';
        CREATE DATABASE cloudtest WITH OWNER devuser ENCODING 'UTF8' LC_COLLATE = 'en_US.UTF8' LC_CTYPE = 'en_US.UTF8' TEMPLATE template0;
        GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE cloudtest TO devuser;
EOF
~~~

paragraphs.title: 3 - Create the call_center table
paragraphs.text:
%psql

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS call_center;

CREATE TABLE call_center (
                                      cc_call_center_sk INT NOT NULL,
                                      cc_call_center_id VARCHAR(16) NOT NULL,
                                      cc_rec_start_date DATE,
                                      cc_rec_end_date DATE,
                                      cc_closed_date_sk DATE,
                                      cc_open_date_sk VARCHAR(12),
                                      cc_name VARCHAR(64),
                                      cc_class VARCHAR(64),
                                      cc_employees INT,
                                      cc_sq_ft INT,
                                      cc_hours VARCHAR(24),
                                      cc_manager VARCHAR(48),
                                      cc_mkt_id INT,
                                      cc_mkt_class VARCHAR(64),
                                      cc_mkt_desc VARCHAR(128),
                                      cc_market_manager VARCHAR(64),
                                      cc_division INT,
                                      cc_division_name VARCHAR(64),
                                      cc_company INT,
                                      cc_company_name VARCHAR(64),
                                      cc_street_number VARCHAR(12),
                                      cc_street_name VARCHAR(64),
                                      cc_street_type VARCHAR(24),
                                      cc_suite_number VARCHAR(12),
                                      cc_city VARCHAR(64),
                                      cc_county VARCHAR(64),
                                      cc_state CHAR(2),
                                      cc_zip VARCHAR(12),
                                      cc_country VARCHAR(24),
                                      cc_gmt_offset INT,
                                      cc_tax_percentage DECIMAL(5,2),
                                      junk CHAR(2),
                                      primary key (cc_call_center_sk)
                                      );
